| 2nd generation GRT (Group Rapid Transit) vehicles accommodate up to 24 passengers (12 seated). The vehicles operate on-schedule during peak hours, at a 2.5 minute interval, and can operate on demand during off-peak hours. The current system will operate until the end of 2018, after which it is expected to be replaced and expanded.&lt;ref&gt;{{cite web|title=RIVIUM GRT|url=https://www.2getthere.eu/projects/rivium-grt/|publisher=2getthere|accessdate=1 September 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170310200020/http://www.2getthere.eu/projects/rivium-grt/|archive-date=2017-03-10|url-status=dead}}.  I pilot scheme operated on part of the current route between 1999 and 2005.&lt;/ref&gt;
